{"id":2298,"date":"2021-12-23T21:07:09","date_gmt":"2021-12-23T20:07:09","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/?page_id=2298"},"modified":"2022-11-22T11:26:46","modified_gmt":"2022-11-22T10:26:46","slug":"crowdfunding-events","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/crowdfunding-events\/","title":{"rendered":"Crowdfunding Events"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"modal-ready\">\n<p>In December 2021, the OPERAS Crowdfunding Initiative was <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/2021\/12\/cf-initiative-launched\/\" target=\"_blank\">launched<\/a>. The Initiative is a collaboration between the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.operas-eu.org\/\" target=\"_blank\">OPERAS Research Infrastructure<\/a> and the crowdfunding platform <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/wemakeit.com\/\" target=\"_blank\">wemakeit.com<\/a>, and it is through the TRIPLE Project that this collaboration is brought to life. Researchers from Social Sciences and Humanities (SSH) disciplines are invited to launch a campaign to finance their project ideas. More information can be found on the <a href=\"https:\/\/wemakeit.com\/pages\/operas\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">OPERAS Channel<\/a> on the wemakeit platform.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:10px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wemakeit.com\/pages\/operas\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/operas-channel.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2276\" width=\"164\" height=\"164\" srcset=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/operas-channel.png 300w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/operas-channel-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/operas-channel-270x270.png 270w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/operas-channel-230x230.png 230w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 164px) 100vw, 164px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>You are intrigued and want to know more about the OPERAS Crowdfunding Channel works? Click <a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/guidelines-for-submission\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/guidelines-for-submission\/\">here <\/a>for more info on the process.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You have questions?  Have a look at our FAQs <a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/faqs-operas-crowdfunding-channel\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/faqs-operas-crowdfunding-channel\/\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>List of Upcoming Crowdfunding Events<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The are no upcoming events for the moment.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h2>List of Past Crowdfunding Events<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h4>Scientific Crowdfunding Workshop 18th November 2022 <\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Are you curious about what crowdfunding can do for you, and for the Social Sciences and Humanities (SSH)? Just one hint: it is not just about money.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Join us on Friday, 18th November 2022 at 14:00 CEST for a short introduction workshop. Our science crowdfunding experts will provide you with the tips and tools to understand what crowdfunding is, how it can be applied to science, and how to launch your own campaign to collect financial support from the crowd, but also communicate your research in the most exciting format.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The presentation will be followed by 30 minutes of Q&amp;A &#8211; we want to make sure you have all the information you need to get started with your project.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: the workshop was organised in French and English in two separate sessions which took place contemporaneously. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\ud83d\uddd3 Date: <strong>Friday, 18 November 2022, 14.00 \u2013 14.45 (CEST)<\/strong><br>\ud83e\udd35  Hosts: Emilie Bloti\u00e8re, Lottie Provost, Sona Arasteh (english)<br>\ud83d\udccc Venue: Virtual event via Zoo link will be provided after registration<br>\ud83d\udccb Download the slides here: <a href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.7261427\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.7261427<\/a> (from the workshop held on 28 October 2022)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Scientific Crowdfunding Workshop 28th October 2022 <\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Are you curious about what crowdfunding can do for you, and for the Social Sciences and Humanities (SSH)? Just one hint: it is not just about money.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Join us on Friday, 28th October 2022 at 14:00 CEST for a short introduction workshop. Our science crowdfunding experts will provide you with the tips and tools to understand what crowdfunding is, how it can be applied to science, and how to launch your own campaign to collect financial support from the crowd, but also communicate your research in the most exciting format.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The presentation was followed by 30 minutes of Q&amp;A to make sure you have all the information you need to get started with your project.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: the workshop was organised in French and English in two separate sessions which took place contemporaneously. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\ud83d\uddd3 Date: <strong>Friday, 28 October 2022, 14.00 \u2013 14.45 (CEST)<\/strong><br>\ud83e\udd35  Hosts: Emilie Bloti\u00e8re, Lottie Provost, Sona Arasteh (english)<br>\ud83d\udccc Venue:<a href=\"https:\/\/us06web.zoom.us\/j\/86473465461\"> <\/a>Virtual event via Zoom<br>\ud83d\udccb Download the slides here: <a href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.7261427\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.7261427<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Scientific Crowdfunding Workshop 24th May 2022<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Are you curious about what crowdfunding can do for you, and for the Social Sciences and Humanities (SSH)? Just on